    {
        "content": "<p>LaoLittle edited a <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12697#issuecomment-3977917613\">comment</a> on <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/12697\">PR #12697</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Hi, if I use ty_int_ref_scalar_64, the tests will produce new errors such as</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>That's pretty surprising: it should be equivalent to the composition of the two matchers you used, and triggering other errors is indicative of something we should fix, not run away from.</p>\n<p>It looks like <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/4fd25c073d4cbfc4aeed40ea229f327fc0f6ffe8/cranelift/codegen/src/isle_prelude.rs#L282-L288\">the definition</a> is about what I would expect, except that maybe it's missing a check for <code>!is_dynamic_vector</code> -- would you mind adding that as well and trying again?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thanks for clarifying! I've patched the <code>ty_int_ref_scalar_64</code> and it works without errors across all of the clif tests.</p>\n</blockquote>",
